<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000045#     1#       361.38#">Va. Code Ann. § 45.1-361.38</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_45.1-361.38"/><heading><desig>§ 45.1-361.38.</desig><title>Report of permitted activities and production required; contents</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Each holder of a permit for gas or oil wells or gathering pipelines shall file monthly and annual reports of his activities as prescribed by the Director. These reports shall be for the purpose of obtaining information regarding the production and sale of gas and oil resources, as well as information concerning the ownership and control of permitted activities. Filing of these reports by a permittee shall be a condition of such permit. Every annual report filed by a permittee shall contain a certification that such permittee has paid all severance taxes levied under the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 58.1-3712"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 58.1-3712">§§ 58.1-3712<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000058#     1#         3712#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 58.1-3713"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 58.1-3713">58.1-3713<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000058#     1#         3713#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 58.1-3741"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 58.1-3741">58.1-3741<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000058#     1#         3741#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> At the same time that a permittee files the monthly and annual reports as required by subsection A, the permittee shall send copies of the reports by mail to the commissioner of revenue of the political subdivision where the permitted wells are located.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1990 VA CH 92"><content><span normalizedCite="1990 Va. Ch. 92">1990, c. 92<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1990#000092#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1992 VA CH 361"><content><span normalizedCite="1992 Va. Ch. 361">1992, c. 361<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1992#000361#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2013 VA CH 305"><content><span normalizedCite="2013 Va. Ch. 305">2013, cc. 305<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2013#000305#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="2013 VA CH 618"><content><span normalizedCite="2013 Va. Ch. 618">618<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2013#000618#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2016 VA CH 305"><content><span normalizedCite="2016 Va. Ch. 305">2016, c. 305<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1